<div id="wiki-tab-0-2" style="display:none">
<h1 id="toc9"><span><strong>Script Templates</strong></span></h1>
<p>Of course people are welcome to write audio scripts however they like, but this is a useful semi-standardized template for a format that is easy for a producer/director/sound engineer/actor to work from.</p>
<hr />
<p><strong>Example Script Template (Wiki code; copy &amp; paste this into your sandbox):</strong></p>
<p><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">**Title:**&#32;(Work&#32;Title)</span><br />
<span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">**Characters:**</span><br />
<span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">*&#32;(Character&#32;A):&#32;Brief&#32;Description&#32;of&#32;Character&#32;A,&#32;including&#32;notes&#32;for&#32;voice&#32;actor&#32;casting</span><br />
<span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">*&#32;(Character&#32;B):&#32;Brief&#32;Description&#32;of&#32;Character&#32;B,&#32;including&#32;notes&#32;for&#32;voice&#32;actor&#32;casting</span><br />
<span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">*&#32;Etc.</span></p>
<p><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">**Script**</span></p>
<p><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">//(Description&#32;of&#32;ambiance,&#32;i.e.&#32;&quot;Sounds&#32;of&#32;a&#32;forest&#32;at&#32;night&quot;)//</span></p>
<p><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">**CHARACTER&#32;A:**&#32;I&#32;say&#32;some&#32;line&#32;of&#32;dialogue&#32;here.</span></p>
<p><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">**CHARACTER&#32;B:**&#32;I&#32;say&#32;something&#32;else&#32;here,&#32;such&#32;as&#32;replying&#32;to&#32;Character&#32;A,&#32;or&#32;whatever.</span></p>
<p><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">//(Description&#32;of&#32;sounds&#32;heard,&#32;i.e.&#32;&quot;A&#32;low&#32;howl&#32;is&#32;heard&#32;in&#32;the&#32;distance&quot;)//</span></p>
<p><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">**CHARACTER&#32;A:**&#32;Hey,&#32;did&#32;you&#32;hear&#32;that&#32;thing&#32;that&#32;sounded&#32;like&#32;a&#32;low&#32;howl&#32;in&#32;the&#32;distance?</span></p>
<p>(This continues)</p>
<p><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">**FINAL&#32;NOTE:**&#32;An&#32;(optional)&#32;reference&#32;putting&#32;context&#32;into&#32;how&#32;the&#32;Foundation&#32;came&#32;to&#32;have&#32;this&#32;recording.</span></p>
<p><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">**End&#32;of&#32;script**</span></p>
<hr />
<p><strong>This, of course, would end up looking like this (when formatted):</strong></p>
<hr />
<p><strong>Title:</strong> (Work Title)<br />
<strong>Characters:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>(Character A): Brief Description of Character A, including notes for voice actor casting</li>
<li>(Character B): Brief Description of Character B, including notes for voice actor casting</li>
<li>Etc.</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Script</strong></p>
<p><em>(Description of ambiance, i.e. &quot;Sounds of a forest at night&quot;)</em></p>
<p><strong>CHARACTER A:</strong> I say some line of dialogue here.</p>
<p><strong>CHARACTER B:</strong> I say something else here, such as replying to Character A, or whatever.</p>
<p><em>(Description of sounds heard, i.e. &quot;A low howl is heard in the distance&quot;)</em></p>
<p><strong>CHARACTER A:</strong> Hey, did you hear that thing that sounded like a low howl in the distance?</p>
<p>(This continues)</p>
<p><strong>FINAL NOTE:</strong> An (optional) reference putting context into how the Foundation came to have this recording.</p>
<p><strong>End of script</strong></p>
</div>
<div id="wiki-tab-0-3" style="display:none">
<h1 id="toc10"><span><strong>Works In Progress</strong></span></h1>
<p><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">THIS IS NOT THE LOCATION TO POST THE WORKS THEMSELVES, RATHER, JUST POST LINKS TO YOUR AUDIO SANDBOX! ALSO, DON'T USE THE MAIN WIKI FOR INCOMPLETE WORKS; USE <a href="/sandbox">A SANDBOX</a> INSTEAD.</span></strong></p>
<p>Unlike writing an SCP or a Foundation Tale, audio projects are often collaborative efforts that require a number of people (writer, director, sound engineer, voice actors, SFX (sound effects) creator). If you're working on something, use this as an index for your project. <em>(This assumes you're a writer in search of assistance; if you are instead a sound engineer, voice actor, SFX artist, or the like, go to the &quot;Volunteers&quot; tab.)</em> Please place your name in alphabetical order.</p>
<p>Similarly, partial audio clips (such as lines read by a particular individual for a given work) should be uploaded to the writer's sandbox page. <strong>Do not upload such audio clips to this page.</strong></p>
<hr />
<h2 id="toc11"><span><strong>Works In Progress By Author</strong></span></h2>
<blockquote>
<p><strong>Dr. X. Ample</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>&quot;Work Title&quot; <em>(hyperlinked to sandbox)</em>
<ul>
